'''Julian Glover''' [[Wikipedia:Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (born [[March 27]], [[1930s#1935|1935]])<ref name="This Week! Ep9" /> is an [[Wikipedia:English people|English]] actor who played [[General]] [[Maximilian Veers]] in [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']]. He is best known for his roles as [[W:c:jamesbond:Aris Kristatos|Aris Kristatos]] in the [[1981]] ''James Bond'' film [[Wikipedia:For Your Eyes Only (film)|''For Your Eyes Only'']], [[W:c:indianajones:Walter Donovan|Walter Donovan]] in the [[1989]] film [[Wikipedia:Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade|''Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade'']], the voice of the giant spider [[W:c:harrypotter:Aragog|Aragog]] in the [[2002]] film [[Wikipedia:Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets (film)|''Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets'']], and Grand Maester [[W:c:gameofthrones:Pycelle|Pycelle]] in the HBO series [[Wikipedia:Game of Thrones|''Game of Thrones'']]. He was also featured alongside fellow Star Wars alumni [[Alec Guinness]] ([[Obi-Wan Kenobi]]) as Hermann Fegelein in ''Hitler: The Last Ten Days''.

His son, [[Jamie Glover]], provided the voice of Veers in ''[[Star Wars: Battlefront II]]'' and ''[[Star Wars: Empire at War]]''. Jamie also voiced the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] [[Darth Malgus]] in the ''[[Deceived]]'' trailer for ''[[Star Wars: The Old Republic]]''.

